## DRY (Don't Repeat Yourself) & Reusable Components

* **Always apply the DRY principle** — avoid duplicating code, logic, or styling.
* **Create reusable components** when the same pattern appears 2+ times.
* **Share types/interfaces** — define once in shared type files, import where needed.
* Check `packages/media-viewer`, `packages/media-store`, `packages/shared-contracts`, and `packages/media-metadata-core` before creating new utilities.

---

## Documentation

Project documentation lives in `docs/`:
* **`END-USER-GUIDE/`** — non-technical user docs (overview, install)
* **`PRODUCT-FEATURES/`** — product/UX specs by module (`AI/`, `media-library/`, `installer/`, `metadata/`)
* **`IMPLEMENTATION-LOG/`** — feature, bug, and refactoring records
* **`ROADMAP/`** — planned features
* **`ARCHITECTURE/`** — technical architecture docs

---

## Cursor Generation Rules

* Default to typed, small, reusable functions.
* Never expose environment secrets.
* **Always follow DRY principles** — create reusable components instead of duplicating code.
* Ensure imports follow alias structure (e.g. `@emk/media-store`, `@emk/shared-contracts`).
* **Check for existing reusable components** before creating new ones.

---

## Testing & Linting

* ESLint must be configured.
* Vitest for unit and component tests. Playwright for E2E.
* Every extracted module from refactoring must have at least basic unit tests.
* See `testing-standards.mdc` for full testing conventions.
